OL,7,F"Police and ambulance attended, and Mr
OL,8,FHayes was taken to hospital by
OL,9,Fparamedics to receive treatment. Mr
OL,10,FHayes' injuries were assessed by
OL,11,Fmedical professionals as not believed
OL,12,Fto be life threatening, and it was
OL,13,Fdetermined that the investigation did
OL,14,Fnot meet the criteria for a referral
OL,15,Fto our Serious Collisions Unit, where
OL,16,Fa family liaison officer would usually
OL,17,Fbe deployed to inform the next of kin.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G7/9
